Empower your kids to love coding

Junior offers one-on-one live lessons in programming and computer science

A new way to learn

Junior Learning provides online coding classes with a private instructor. Each student meets with their instructor once or twice a week, privately or in a small group setting (up to 3 students). Developed by Stanford graduates and Google alumni, our program develops bright minds ages 5-18 using our curriculum and digital tools. Students leave the program with confidence in pursuing technical topics and knowledge of how to build games, apps, and websites.

Junior Jr: Scratch
Ages 5-7 (Beginners)

Junior Jr provides a fun introduction to programming for our youngest students. In Junior Jr, students learn about logic, sequencing, loops, and events. They also practice fundamental skills like basic algebra, reading, and public speaking. Together, we build games, solve puzzles, and design art.

No subsequent courses!

Junior course explorer

Students start on one of our tracks and progress through levels as they advance. Each track typically takes 3-6 months to complete, with additional project modules if students would like a more in-depth experience.

"Junior was there for me."

Pricing

Each pass is billed on a monthly basis for the allotted pass length and comes with a free class. All packages include a preliminary assessment, resource recommendations, and follow-up counseling. Cancel your subscription at any time and we'll be happy to discontinue pass billing with no fees.
